<section id="sect-00001">
<title>Infrared Spectroscopy</title>
<para id="para-00001">Ethers are difficult to identify by IR spectroscopy. Although they show an absorption due to C–O single-bond stretching in the range 1050 to 1150 cm<sup>–1</sup>, many other kinds of absorptions occur in the same range. <link target-id="fig-00001"/> shows the IR spectrum of diethyl ether and identifies the C–O stretch. Phenyl alkyl ethers show two strong absorbances for C–O stretching at 1050 and 1250 cm<sup>–1</sup>. <link target-id="fig-00002"/> shows the IR spectrum of anisole.</para>
<figure class="scaled-down" id="fig-00001">
<media alt="An illustration shows the infrared spectrum of diethyl ether. The horizontal axis labeled “Wavenumber (centimeter superscript minus 1) is marked in decreasing order starting from 4000 to 500 at equal intervals of 500 units. The “Transmittance in percentage” is shown on the vertical axis starting from 0 to 100 percent at equal interval of 20. The graph starts a little above the 90 mark on the vertical axis. Between wavelengths of 3000 and 2800 2 troughs of uneven lengths are shown with the lowest trough around 3000; between 1500 and 1000 many uneven troughs are shown the lowest one between 1200 and 1100 and is labeled “C-O stretch.”">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/OChem_18_09_001.jpg"/>
</media>
<caption><emphasis effect="bold">The infrared spectrum of diethyl ether, CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>OCH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>3</sub></emphasis>.</caption>
</figure>
<figure class="scaled-down" id="fig-00002">
<media alt="An illustration shows the infrared spectrum of anisole wherein the horizontal axis shows wavenumbers in cm to the power minus one starting from 4000 on the left side to 400 on the right side at the interval of 400 cm to the power minus one till 2000 and from thereafter at the interval of 200 cm to the power minus one till 200; the vertical axis shows transmittance in percentage starting from 0 to 100 at the interval of 20 percent. The upper part of the horizontal axis shows microns starting from 2.5 on the left side to 25 on the right side at the interval of approximately 1 micron. The graph starts a little above the 90 mark on the vertical axis. Between wavenumbers of 3000 and 2800 and between 3 and 4 microns many troughs of uneven lengths are shown with the lowest trough around 3100 labeled “sp superscript 2 C-H stretch;” around 3000 labeled “sp superscript 2 C-H stretch” between 1500 and 1000 many uneven troughs are shown the lowest one between 1200 and 1100 and is labeled “C-O stretch.” Between wavenumbers of 1600 and 1000 and between 6 and 10 microns many troughs of uneven lengths are shown. The troughs at the beginning and end between 1600 and 1500 are labeled “aromatic alkenes.” Between wavenumbers of 1600 and 1000 and between 6 and 10 microns many troughs of uneven lengths are shown. Two long troughs between 1300 and 1000 and between 7.5 and 10 microns are labeled “C-O stretch.” Between wavenumbers of 800 and 700 and between 12 and 15 microns the troughs are labeled “mono subst. oop.” The structure of benzene methoxide is shown as benzene bonded to methoxide group.">
