<media alt="An illustration shows 2 structures. The structure of methyl propyl ether shows a methyl group bonded to an oxygen atom bonded to a methylene group bonded to a second methylene group bonded to a methyl group. The carbon atom of the methyl group oxygen atom and the carbon atom of the first methylene group are shown in pink. The carbon atom of the methyl group is labeled 58.5 delta; carbon atom of the first methylene group (bonded to the oxygen atom) is labeled 74.8 delta; carbon atom of the second methylene group is 23.3 delta; carbon atom of the methyl group is 10.7 delta. The structure of anisole shows a benzene. C1 is bonded to an oxygen atom bonded to a methyl group. C1 is highlighted in a small pink circle and is labeled 159.9 delta; The carbon atom of the methyl group is highlighted in pink and is labeled 54.8 delta. C2 is labeled 114.1 delta; C3 is labeled 129.5 delta and C4 is labeled 120.7 delta.">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/OChem_18_09_005.jpg"/>
</media>
</figure>
